\f3\fs20 Push for slavery reparations is misguided effort
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 The demand for reparations for the past practice of slavery goes on despite it being almost impossible to identify just who had ancestors who were slaves in America. Reparations has a dubious foundation, given how the United States passed myriad Great Society programs that actually made Black Americans more dependent on government and led to the effective destruction of the Black family in many instances. New handouts would not address core problems many Black people face, like single-parent families and high levels of crime. These are largely the product of today's welfare state, not slavery. To blame slavery ignores the fact that after the Civil War, the Black family had become quite strong - that is, until the welfare state destroyed it. One could once accurately say the legacy of slavery was damaging to Black America, but now the blame can be placed at the feet of government and the "race hustle" of some Black leaders and the Democratic Party.
