\f3\fs20 \cf0 Things to do if you like to breathe
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 I grew up in Los Angeles. I remember feeling ill each year when summer approached and smog was at its worst. As part of my nurses' training, I took a pulmonary function test. The test revealed I had only 50 percent lung function. I've never been a smoker, nor did I grow up in a smoking household. The technician explained that it was most likely due to the smog I had lived in my entire life.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 I have lived in Atlanta since 1997. In that time, I have seen the fights over expanding MARTA, worsening traffic and sky-high rates of asthma and allergies. We have to get serious about improving our environment. Here's what I'd like to see us do: Promote expanded public transportation to decrease traffic; promote alternatives to fossil fuels, such as solar and wind power; and place a fee on carbon that will be passed on to each consumer who can then use that money to pay for solar panels, etc. I want to breathe. Don't you? DEBRA GREENWOOD, STONE MOUNTAIN
