\f3\fs20 \cf0 DEBATE
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 Format, moderator were biggest losers
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 Much has been said about who "won" the first presidential debate of 2012. Clearly, President Obama should have been more aggressive concerning Mitt Romney, who was acting like the schoolyard bully he is. However, the biggest "loser" was the format, as well as the moderator.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 The format was nothing more than a bar-room argument without any rules or controls. Mr. Lehrer didn't control the debate at all, and that is why the debate was nothing more than an argument between a schoolyard bully, and one too detached. Debates must have structure, procedure and rules to show who has the best argument.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 D.M. SMITH, MARIETTA
\f0\fs24 \
